Literally just started playing, but I can already tell I'm gonna love it. Will update as I play. The color options are much better than previous simulators. The sounds and visuals are delightful, as always. The haze and the sun effects are very life-like. The rock and dirt textures are stunning. The fox turns a bit too sharply to allow for precise and subtle direction change, as in the other ultimate sims, but I'll try to get used to it. Perhaps adding a direction pad sensitivity option in future sims would help suit people's preferences. The fact that the fox turns its head before changing direction makes it look much more natural. Alright, the fox can eat some non-meat items! Nice ripple effect when the fox swims. Sometimes, swiping the camera doesn't turn the view and stays behind the fox. There is still that flicker glitch when the settings are on high quality. When I confront strong enemies, and I try to flee, the map view goes crazy and the fox just runs in circles around the enemy until it dies. I can't get away to regenerate my health. Hoping for an ultimate cheetah sim with adjustable speed controls(flight altitude buttons) and swaying tail while running! *crosses fingers*
